ALGORITHMS AND METHODS (ADAPTED / IMPLEMENTED IN-REPO)
------------------------------------------------------

The following describes logic implemented in this codebase. It is provided for
transparency, not as a claim of novelty or clinical validity.

1. Tobii Ghost overlay — Hough circle detection (server-side)
   - Files: sorot.py, gaze_post_processor.py, validation_points.py,
     legacy/tests/test_roi_gaze_webapp.py
   - Method: OpenCV cv2.HoughCircles on grayscale frames (median blur,
     HOUGH_GRADIENT) to locate a circular gaze marker in recorded video.
   - Parameters (e.g. param1/param2, min/max radius) are empirically tuned for
     lab capture setups; they are not supplied by Tobii.
   - Basis: Classical circle Hough transform as implemented in OpenCV
     (see OpenCV attribution below).

2. Tobii Ghost overlay — color-threshold marker detection (client-side)
   - File: frontend/src/workers/analyzerWorker.ts
   - Method: Heuristic BGRA/RGBA thresholding for cyan ring and bright core
     colors associated with the Tobii Ghost on-screen indicator, plus centroid
     of matched pixels; optional pixel stride for performance.
   - Basis: In-house lab tuning on OBS-captured footage; independent of Tobii
     SDK APIs. Documented in source comments for reproducibility.

3. Fixation grouping (velocity-threshold style, simplified)
   - File: sorot.py (trajectory / fixation visualization)
   - Method: Sequential gaze points grouped while successive samples remain
     within a spatial radius (FIXATION_RADIUS) for a minimum frame count.
   - Basis: Common dispersion-threshold fixation concept used in eye-tracking
     literature; this implementation is a simplified teaching/research variant,
     not a certified I-DT or I-VT classifier.

4. Gaze heatmaps
   - Files: sorot.py and related processing paths
   - Method: 2D histogram of gaze positions with Gaussian smoothing
     (OpenCV/numpy).
   - Basis: Standard density-estimation visualization practice.

5. ROI hit testing and metrics
   - Files: frontend (e.g. gazeRoi.ts), sorot.py API layers
   - Method: Axis-aligned bounding boxes and scene frame ranges for dwell /
     entry statistics.
   - Basis: Standard computational geometry; no external algorithm source
     copied.

6. Optional integrations
   - OBS WebSocket (obs-websocket-py): start/stop recording when configured.
   - yt-dlp: download stimulus videos when permitted by site terms.
   - Virtual camera index: reads frames from a user-selected capture device.

